# GitHub Pages setup for DHC-6 Trainer website

This package is prepared for GitHub Pages project hosting.

## Publish settings

Repository: `dhc6-trainer-website`

GitHub → repo → Settings → Pages:

- Source: Deploy from a branch
- Branch: main
- Folder: /root

After publishing, GitHub will show the live URL. Use these Play Console URLs after replacing `YOUR-GITHUB-USERNAME` with the published owner shown by GitHub:

- Website: `https://YOUR-GITHUB-USERNAME.github.io/dhc6-trainer-website/`
- Privacy Policy: `https://YOUR-GITHUB-USERNAME.github.io/dhc6-trainer-website/privacy.html`
- Account/Data Deletion: `https://YOUR-GITHUB-USERNAME.github.io/dhc6-trainer-website/account-deletion.html`

## Notes

- `.nojekyll` is included so GitHub Pages serves this as plain static HTML.
- All internal links are relative, so the site works from the GitHub Pages project path.
- The Play Store link remains a coming-soon placeholder while closed testing is in progress.
